<div class='allCommunityAnswers'>
<div class='communityAnswer'>
<div class='communityAnswerBody'>
<div class='answererUserIcon'>
<a class="leftAlignedImage userPhoto" href="/user/show/93368396-madeline"><img alt="" src="https://s.gr-assets.com/assets/nophoto/user/u_100x100-259587f1619f5253426a4fa6fb508831.png" /></a>
</div>
<div class='communityAnswerTextContainer'>
<span class='communityAnswererName'>
<a href="/user/show/93368396-madeline">Madeline</a>
</span>
<span class='communityAnswerText'>
<div class='spoiler'>
This answer contains spoilers…
<span class='spoilerAnswerText'>
<a class="jsShowSpoiler spoilerAction">(view spoiler)</a><span class="spoilerContainer" style="display: none">[
  
    Someone already answered this above - it's not obvious but I think it's implied that she's dead. Based on the American criminal having her homework, i<a href="#" rel="nofollow noopener">…more</a>
    Someone already answered this above - it's not obvious but I think it's implied that she's dead. Based on the American criminal having her homework, it seems like she was hiding him at some point. I think her character was there to draw a comparison between the priest and the bank robber - an innocent child who was trying to do the right thing (in a secular sense) saw them as no different. Perhaps she represented the pure compassion and mercy that the priest failed to feel for anyone but his daughter?<a href="#" rel="nofollow noopener">(less)</a>
  
 <a class="jsHideSpoiler spoilerAction">(hide spoiler)</a>]</span>
</span>
</div>
</span>
</div>
